    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-07-05T13:53:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-07-05T13:53:00-05:00" n="724"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d724">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.91/7–552: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in India</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d724fn1">This telegram was repeated for information to
                        Karachi, London, and New York.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-07-05T14:53:00-04:00"
                            >July 5, 1952—2:53 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>42. For: the Ambassador re Kashmir. We presume you will want to keep in mind, in
                    talking to <persName corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName>, <gloss target="#t_Dept1"
                        >Dept</gloss>’s tel to <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> re our
                    suggestion to <persName corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName> that, after he has
                    been informed that you have presented <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss>
                    proposals to <persName corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName>, he then informally say
                    to <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_IN1">Ind</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_REP1">rep</gloss>s in NY that, having learned certain informal
                    discussions on Kashmir had been initiated in subcontinent, he wishes to suspend
                    negots in NY until outcome of discussions in subcontinent known. Assuming
                        <persName corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName> agrees, we hope this will
                    enable you to bring pressure to bear on <persName corresp="#p_NJ1"
                        >Nehru</persName> to make specific reply to <gloss target="#t_Pak1"
                        >Pak</gloss> proposals, since <persName corresp="#p_GDF1">Graham</persName>
                    wld in fact not be continuing negots of his own until he knew outcome of
                    discussions in subcontinent.</p>
                <p>If <persName corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName> endeavors avoid responsibility of
                    making direct reply to <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> proposal by raising
                    question of alternative approaches to solution such as partition you shld
                    endeavor avoid discussing alternatives until such time as <persName
                        corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName> has given you reply and you have
                    transmitted this to Karachi. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> considers it
                    of greatest importance that in these talks you avoid any possible situation
                    wherein it mght be alleged that you compromised <gloss target="#t_GOP1"
                        >GOP</gloss> proposals in course of conversation with <persName
                        corresp="#p_NJ1">Nehru</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BDKE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bruce</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
